UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 76
1 AN ACT relating to use of a credit card or debit card.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 369.135 is repealed, reenacted as a new section of KRS Chapter
4 365, and amended to read as follows:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Credit card" means an instrument or device, which may be in tangible or
7 electronic form, that is issued by a business organization or financial
8 institution for use by a cardholder to obtain goods, services, or anything else
9 of value on credit;
10 (b) "Debit card":
11 1. Except as provided in subparagraph 2. of this paragraph, means an
12 instrument or device, which may be in tangible or electronic form, that
13 is issued by a business organization or financial institution for use by
14 a cardholder to obtain goods, services, or anything else of value,
15 where payment for the goods, the services, or anything else of value is
16 made using funds previously deposited by the cardholder; and
17 2. Does not include a check, draft, or other negotiable instrument,
18 whether in paper or electronic form;
19 (c) "Digital asset" has the same meaning as in KRS 369.130; and
20 (d) "Wallet" has the same meaning as in KRS 369.130.
21 (2) An individual shall not be prohibited from:
22 (a) Accepting a digital asset, credit card, or debit card as a method of[digital
23 assets for] payment for legal goods or services; or
24 (b) The use of a wallet.
25 (3)[(2)] A digital asset, credit card, or debit card[Digital assets] used as a method of
26 payment shall not be subject to additional taxes, withholdings, assessments, or
27 charges that are based solely on the use of the digital asset, credit card, or debit
