1 card as the method of payment.
2 (4)[(3)] This section shall not:
3 (a) Prohibit the imposition or collection of taxes, withholdings, assessments, or
4 charges on a digital asset, credit card, or debit card[digital assets] used as the
5 method of payment when the same imposition and collections of taxes,
6 withholdings, assessments, or charges are made on similar transactions which
7 use the legal tender of the United States as the method of payment; or
8 (b) Require any person to accept a digital asset, credit card, or debit card as a
9 method of[digital assets for] payment for legal goods or services.
